# Deploy StockFolio for Free with a Real Database

Deploy the full-stack StockFolio app to the public internet using free-tier services.

## Deployment Stack (All Free Tier)

| Service | Provider | Free Tier |
|---|---|---|
| **Next.js (frontend + API)** | [Vercel](https://vercel.com) | Unlimited deploys, serverless functions, global CDN |
| **PostgreSQL Database** | [Neon](https://neon.tech) | 0.5 GB storage, always-on, branching |
| **FastAPI (market data)** | [Render](https://render.com) | 750 hrs/month, auto-deploy from Git, spins down after 15 min inactivity |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Render free tier** spins down after 15 minutes of inactivity. First request after idle takes ~30–60 seconds (cold start). This is fine for a portfolio project.

## User Steps Required (Manual — Outside of Code)

These steps must be done by the user in a web browser:

1. **Create accounts** on [Vercel](https://vercel.com), [Neon](https://neon.tech), and [Render](https://render.com) (all have GitHub login)
2. **Neon** — Create a free PostgreSQL database and copy the connection string
3. **Vercel** — Import the GitHub repo, set root directory to `apps/web`, configure env vars
4. **Render** — Create a new Web Service from the repo, set root directory to `services/market-data`

## Proposed Code Changes

### Prisma Schema — Switch to PostgreSQL

#### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/shubh/OneDrive/Documents/my-portfolio/packages/db/prisma/schema.prisma)
- Change `provider = "sqlite"` → `provider = "postgresql"`
- This is the **only** schema change needed. All models already use `cuid()`, `DateTime`, and standard types that work identically on both databases.

---

### Prisma Client — Remove SQLite Fallback

#### [MODIFY] [prisma.ts](file:///c:/Users/shubh/OneDrive/Documents/my-portfolio/apps/web/src/lib/prisma.ts)
- Remove the `getDatabaseUrl()` fallback that constructs a SQLite path
- Use `env("DATABASE_URL")` directly (Vercel will inject the Neon URL)

---

### Next.js Config — Standalone Output for Vercel

#### [MODIFY] [next.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/shubh/OneDrive/Documents/my-portfolio/apps/web/next.config.ts)
- Add `output: "standalone"` for optimized Vercel deployment
- Add `serverExternalPackages: ["bcryptjs"]` to handle native Node modules

---

### Vercel Config — Monorepo Setup

#### [NEW] [vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/shubh/OneDrive/Documents/my-portfolio/vercel.json)
- Configure the build command to generate Prisma client before `next build`
- Set install and root directory for monorepo

---

### Render Config — FastAPI Deployment

#### [NEW] [render.yaml](file:///c:/Users/shubh/OneDrive/Documents/my-portfolio/render.yaml)
- Blueprint for auto-deploying the FastAPI service from the `services/market-data` directory
- Sets `uvicorn main:app` as the start command

