## Environment Variables (Production)

### Vercel (Next.js)
| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `DATABASE_URL` | Neon PostgreSQL connection string |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Random 64+ char secret |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` | `https://your-app.vercel.app` |
| `MARKET_DATA_API_URL` | `https://your-service.onrender.com` |
| `MAILER_PROVIDER` | `smtp` |
| `SMTP_HOST` / `SMTP_USER` / `SMTP_PASS` | Gmail SMTP credentials |

### Render (FastAPI)
| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `TWELVE_DATA_API_KEY` | Your Twelve Data API key |
| `GOOGLE_API_KEY` | Google Gemini API key (optional) |

## Verification Plan

1. Push code changes, deploy to Vercel and Render
2. Verify Neon database is reachable (`prisma db push` from local with prod URL)
3. Test registration (OTP), login, portfolio CRUD on the live URL
4. Verify market data proxy hits the Render-hosted FastAPI service
